<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,716,1100]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,716,741]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Disc regularly covered with scales dorsally and naked ventrally, with soft interradial recesses. Absence of bursae. Radial shields partially joined. One lateral oral papilla. Adoral shields all in contact, forming a continuous ring around the mouth. One tentacle scale. Three pointed arm spines (
<bibRefCitation author="Lyman, T." bookContentInfo="203 pp." box="[1055,1200,788,813]" journalOrPublisher="University Press: Welch, Bigelow, &amp; Company, Cambridge" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" refId="ref50591" refString="Lyman, T. (1865) Ophiuridae and Astrophytidae. University Press: Welch, Bigelow, &amp; Company, Cambridge, 203 pp." title="Ophiuridae and Astrophytidae" type="book" year="1865">Lyman 1865</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fell, H. B." box="[1212,1321,788,813]" journalOrPublisher="Zoology Publications from Victoria University of Wellington" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="1 - 44" part="26" refId="ref47348" refString="Fell, H. B. (1960) Synoptic keys to the genera of Ophiuroidea. Zoology Publications from Victoria University of Wellington, 26, 1 - 44." title="Synoptic keys to the genera of Ophiuroidea" type="journal article" year="1960">Fell 1960</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tommasi, L. R." journalOrPublisher="Contribuicoes Avulsas do Instituto Oceanografico, Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="1 - 146" part="20" refId="ref54902" refString="Tommasi, L. R. (1970) Os ofiuroides recentes do Brasil e de regioes vizinhas. Contribuicoes Avulsas do Instituto Oceanografico, Universidade de Sao Paulo, 20, 1 - 146." title="Os ofiuroides recentes do Brasil e de regioes vizinhas" type="journal article" year="1970">Tommasi 1970</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Albuquerque, M. N." bookContentInfo="409 pp." box="[221,435,823,848]" journalOrPublisher="Universidade de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" refId="ref43538" refString="Albuquerque, M. N. (1986) Ophiuroidea Gray, 1840 (Echinodermata) da plataforma continental do norte e nordeste brasileiro. Phd thesis, Universidade de Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, 409 pp." title="Ophiuroidea Gray, 1840 (Echinodermata) da plataforma continental do norte e nordeste brasileiro" type="book" year="1986">Albuquerque 1986</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1437,716,1100]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,860,885]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1865" box="[345,474,860,884]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiactidae" genus="Hemipholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[345,474,860,884]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Hemipholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares features with 
<emphasis box="[721,837,860,884]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lutken" authorityYear="1856" box="[721,833,860,884]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiotrichidae" genus="Ophiactis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">Ophiactis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
such as a ring of contiguous adoral shields and the presence of hemoglobin containing coelomocytes in its water vascular system (
<bibRefCitation author="Christensen, A. B. &amp; Christensen, E. F. &amp; Weisrock, D. W." box="[1034,1297,895,920]" journalOrPublisher="Manine Biology" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="755 - 763" part="154" refId="ref45851" refString="Christensen, A. B., Christensen, E. F. &amp; Weisrock, D. W. (2008) Population genetic structure of North American Ophiactis spp. brittle stars possessing hemoglobin. Manine Biology, 154, 755 - 763. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00227 - 008 - 0968 - 1" title="Population genetic structure of North American Ophiactis spp. brittle stars possessing hemoglobin" type="journal article" year="2008">
Christensen 
<emphasis box="[1175,1224,896,920]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
), suggesting a close systematic relationship between both genera (
<bibRefCitation author="Hendler, G." box="[744,903,932,957]" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="44 - 52" part="3048" refId="ref48483" refString="Hendler, G. (2011) New light on the nomenclature, taxonomy, and biology of Hemipholis species (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea: Ophiactidae). Zootaxa, 3048, 44 - 52." title="New light on the nomenclature, taxonomy, and biology of Hemipholis species (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea: Ophiactidae)" type="journal article" year="2011">Hendler 2011</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1865" box="[921,1050,932,956]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiactidae" genus="Hemipholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[921,1050,932,956]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Hemipholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is well-studied and has repeatedly been cited in ecological, environmental, and biological studies owing to its abundance, broad geographic range, and its remarkable morphological and physiological specializations (
<bibRefCitation author="Hendler, G. &amp; Miller, J. E. &amp; Pawson, D. L. &amp; Kier, P. M." bookContentInfo="390 pp." box="[917,1137,1004,1029]" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" refId="ref48691" refString="Hendler, G., Miller, J. E., Pawson, D. L. &amp; Kier, P. M. (1995) Sea stars, sea urchins, and allies: echinoderms of Florida and the Caribbean. Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington, 390 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / s 0025315400031568" title="Sea stars, sea urchins, and allies: echinoderms of Florida and the Caribbean" type="book" year="1995">
Hendler 
<emphasis box="[1016,1064,1004,1028]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">et al</emphasis>
. 1995
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hendler, G." box="[1148,1305,1004,1029]" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="44 - 52" part="3048" refId="ref48483" refString="Hendler, G. (2011) New light on the nomenclature, taxonomy, and biology of Hemipholis species (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea: Ophiactidae). Zootaxa, 3048, 44 - 52." title="New light on the nomenclature, taxonomy, and biology of Hemipholis species (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea: Ophiactidae)" type="journal article" year="2011">Hendler 2011</bibRefCitation>
). Currently, two species are accepted in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stohr et al. 2016)" authorityName="Stohr et al." authorityYear="2016" box="[479,835,1039,1064]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiactidae" genus="Hemipholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[479,608,1040,1064]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Hemipholis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stohr, S. &amp; Martynov, A." box="[625,827,1039,1064]" journalOrPublisher="PLoS ONE" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="0164562" part="11" refId="ref54292" refString="Stohr, S. &amp; Martynov, A. (2016) Paedomorphosis as an Evolutionary Driving Force: Insights from Deep-Sea Brittle Stars. PLoS ONE, 11, e 0164562. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0164562" title="Paedomorphosis as an Evolutionary Driving Force: Insights from Deep-Sea Brittle Stars" type="journal article" year="2016">
Stöhr 
<emphasis box="[698,750,1040,1064]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, with one recorded from Brazil (
<bibRefCitation author="Barboza, C. A. M. &amp; Borges, M." journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="1 - 21" part="3447" refId="ref44247" refString="Barboza, C. A. M. &amp; Borges, M. (2012) A checklist of the extant species of ophiuroids (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from Brazilian waters. Zootaxa, 3447, 1 - 21." title="A checklist of the extant species of ophiuroids (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from Brazilian waters" type="journal article" year="2012">Barboza &amp; Borges 2012</bibRefCitation>
): 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bosc, 1802)" authorityName="Bosc" authorityYear="1802" baseAuthorityName="Bosc" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[231,625,1076,1100]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiactidae" genus="Hemipholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="cordifera">
<emphasis box="[231,470,1076,1100]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Hemipholis cordifera</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bosc, L. A. G." bookContentInfo="300 pp." box="[485,616,1076,1100]" journalOrPublisher="Chez Deterville, de l'imprimerie de Guilleminet, Paris" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" refId="ref45280" refString="Bosc, L. A. G. (1802) Histoire naturelle des vers, contenant leur description et leurs moeurs; avec figures dessinees d'apres nature. Chez Deterville, de l'imprimerie de Guilleminet, Paris, 300 pp." title="Histoire naturelle des vers, contenant leur description et leurs moeurs; avec figures dessinees d'apres nature" type="book" year="1802">Bosc, 1802</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
